{"html":"<p>Svelte is a next gen web framework that compiles your component code into fast, efficient, vanilla javascript DOM manipulations. </p>\n<p>Nativescript takes the native api surface of iOS and Android and exposes them as vanilla javascript objects.</p>\n<p>Svelte Native is a library that exposes NativeScripts view objects as DOM elements which can be manipulated by Svelte components.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/logos_combined.svg\" alt=\"nativescript + svelte = svelte-native\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"but-doesnt-nativescript-already-offer-vue-and-angular-support\">But doesn&#39;t NativeScript already offer Vue and Angular support?</h3>\n<p>It does!, and they are supported by the nativescript developers. However the marriage of Svelte&#39;s tiny payload size, low boilerplate component definitions, and hyper efficient DOM updates seem like a great fit for mobile development.</p>\n<h3 id=\"what-does-it-look-like\">What does it look like</h3>\n<pre class='language-markup'><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>page</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">xmlns</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>tns<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>page<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>actionBar</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">title</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>Svelte Native App<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><s